Business Brief -- Health Concepts IV Inc.:
   Firm Files for Chapter 11
   After Creditors Call in Debt
Company officials couldn't be reached for comment.
However, in financial statements for its third quarter ended
Aug. 31, the most recent available, the company said a $6
million line of credit from its banks was due to expire Dec.
31.
   The company's bankruptcy filing listed $12.2 million in
assets and $11.1 million in liabilities. For its nine months,
the company had a loss of $2 million, or 73 cents a share, on
revenue of $12.2 million.